# Budget and runway

Canonical math: **`docs/LAUNCH_BUDGET.md`**

## Owner numbers (Jun 2026 baseline)

~**$2,283** cash · affiliate account ~**$630** · target **≥2 months** runway

## Day-1 affiliate stack (minimum)

| Item | ~Cost |
|------|-------|
| Purchased affiliate account | $630 |
| **FastMoss Basic** | ~$59/mo |
| Kling day 1 (8–10 clips + regens) | ~$5–15 |
| Zernio | confirm plan |

**Do not buy for affiliate day 1:** 4 phones · 5th phone · EchoTik · Kalodata

## Monthly affiliate burn (~$420/mo plan number)

FastMoss ~$59 + Zernio/misc ~$100–200 + Kling ~$65–85 + images ~$30–50  
Bubble SIMs ~$50 only when phones live.

## Runway (Plan A — affiliate first)

After account + ~2 months full stack: buffer roughly **$455–525** with FastMoss (better than old EchoTik plan).

## Buy order (speed)

1. Affiliate account  
2. FastMoss subscribe  
3. Zernio → `affiliate_main`  
4. Launch batch (8–10 QC-pass clips)  
5. Bubble hardware ~$280 when ready  

## GOOD vs cheap

**GOOD** = Module 1 QC pass + course edit — not raw Kling output. Regen on fail; don’t brute-force spend on bad prompts.

When numbers change (Zernio tier, cash on hand), suggest updating `LAUNCH_BUDGET.md` — don’t invent new math in chat without checking the doc.
